Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi says his department is done with the placement process. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The online process of placing Gauteng school-age children into their 2020 schools has been completed, according to the Gauteng Education Department. Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi said his department has completed the placement process. READ: Parents criticise Gauteng online school application system The department has removed all applications which did not have the required supporting documents from its allocation list. They will remain on the waiting list until their submissions are complete. Lesufi says there is still space in about 1,033 schools and pupils can be accommodated there.